	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2><br><br>Trukkle lay in his shared room. Zarquon's mess littering the floor. Toolboxes, springs, cogs, greasy books, the occasional glowing bottle of firewater and the even more occasional patch of clean floor, indicating a Gnomish Vanishing Device.<br><br>&quot;Heh, wish he'd invent a Gnomish Cleaning Device&quot; he thinks<br>&quot;you know he'd never do that&quot; the voice of his un-summoned warder whispered &quot;That'd be useful&quot;<br><br>Trukkle laughed his deep chuckle, his warder had started developing a real sense of humor these days. He couldn't even remember the days before this spirit had come to him and shown him the way of the Beastlord.<br><br>Trukkle got up and put on his shaded hopperhide shirt, kilt and shoes. gifts from Drexsanu, a fellow Beastlord, while she was raising her tailoring skills. They had been very welcome as, although Northmen don't like to admit it, Everfrost is a bloody stupid place to wear nothing but a kilt and a pair of sandals.<br><br>Today was the day, he'd have to let the Clan know his family's name, no matter how daft he saw it.<br><br>The only problem was, how?<br><br>'I can't waltz out there and proclaim to all and sundry my last name is .....'<br>he couldn't even bear to think it. His warder took great delight in taking the micky whenever he even thought it.<br><br>&quot;Oh well, I'm sure a way'll come to me&quot; he said to himself and opening the door, trying not to break the clutter it pushed out the way as it swung inwards, walked out to get breakfast <br><br><br>&quot;Well good morning Trukkle!&quot; Drexsys greeted him as he stepped in to the main hall. <br>&quot;Join me for some of these delicious owlbear kabobs that a rather cat looking creature left for us last night. They're quite good.&quot;<br>She raised her hand to offer him a Halas Heater, courtesy of Bildaor who is not present at the moment, and he gladly accepts. <br><br><br><br>Relieved that Drexsys had given him an excuse not to start the task of telling the Clan his name. He sits down and tucks into a kabob.<br><br>&quot;Mmmm Thish ish goobd&quot; <br>Trukkle slurs, through a mouthful of owlbear meat<br><br>&quot;Bit spicy though&quot; he managed reaching for his Halas Heater and taking a deep drink<br><br>&quot;You think?&quot; Drexsys grinned &quot;I thought maybe they aren't spicy enough&quot;<br><br>Zarquon saunters in from outside, clearly trying to pretend he hasn't been running, but his red cheeks and fast breathing give him away.<br><br>He walks through the dining hall, with a grin big enough to put a Cheshire cat to shame<br>&quot;If anyone asks, you think I'm in the stables brushing down Bink. Oh, and you didn't notice me taking a vanishing device out when I went.&quot;<br>He then calmly walked up the stairs<br><br>Drexsys and Trukkle exchange glances, both laughing . Ever since Zarkie had started tinkering, mischief had been his middle name.<br>No more than 5 seconds had passed when Thaylon padded in, still in wolf form, but looking decidedly scruffy.<br><br>&quot;I swear, I'm going to wring that guys neck if i see him&quot; Thaylon murmurs, changing back into his more bipedal form<br>&quot;Don't suppose....&quot;<br>&quot;No we didn't just see Zarkie walk in, and he definitely wasn't carrying a GVD with him&quot; Drexsys laughed &quot;He's been in the stable grooming Bink the whole time&quot;<br><br>&quot;So, what have you been doing then eh?&quot; Trukkle coughs, trying to keep a perfectly straight face &quot;looks like you've been rolling in the bushes, again.&quot;<br><br><br>Thaylon brushes himself off with quick slaps &quot;I swear that gnome is gonna be the death of us&quot; Drexsys turns to Trukkle &quot;beats dying by gnolls&quot; she adds nonchalantly &quot;wasn't to long ago he pulled you out of a bad case of to many gnolls a while back as I recall&quot; Thaylon looks up rising slowly from his brushing &quot;Hmmmmmph always stick up for the little guys don't ya Drex&quot; Drex looks at Thaylon a long friend knowing the little guy has probably just got him a little upset &quot; You know me Thay Always have... always will... it's a weakness let's call it&quot; Thaylon sputters &quot; but he ....he ...pointing after the gnome.......oh nevermind &quot;. &quot;Give me a bottle something with a little kick like the one I want to give Zark!&quot; Drexsys hands over a bottle of elven wine knowing it would help calm the Druid down &quot; Here friend take a bottle of the best I have and sit with Truk and myself and tell us of your recent journeys......&quot; Thaylon starts by telling of a cave on Luclin of rich ore and precious gems.......... <br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>~~My treasures do not clink together or glitter; they gleam in the sun and neigh in the night~~</td></tr>
