<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101817504285980></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101817504285980><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=67676&mid=101817504285980>The Story of the Girl</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=67676&mid=101817504285980#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=67676><span id= >Lady Drexsys</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>9 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Apr 7th 6:28 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The story of the Girl<br><br><br>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br><br>Dlaern walks slowly back to the outpost, his bag heavy with warbraids from the Sarnaks of the Overthere, a small reward had been offered for them. The reward itself was a rather heavy shield so was not appealing to the monk, however he was trying to improve the was he was looked upon, perhaps with enough Braids they would not be so apprehensive.<br><br>He had just given the four from his bag to the Captain when he heard a scream, gaining his attention he looked around for the source, it was during the day he could see around and he saw no signs. Just then a second scream was heard it sounded like it came from the Bank.<br><br>In order not to gain suspicion he walked to the bank, leaving the shield against the wall as he entered, inside was the two mechanical bankers and General D'Veers<br><br>Just then he spotted the source, the General took a swing with some form of whip at a small child near his feet, he was laughing as he beat the helpless kid. Dlaern walked over as calmly as he could, <br><br>A closer look showed the child to be a female Elf, a high elf based on the light complexion, at a guess only 8 years old, maybe more he never was good at guessing ages<br><br>&quot;Hail, General D'Veers, how are you today?&quot; Dlaern asked<br><br>The General turned at him &quot;I am busy, come back another time&quot;<br><br>Dlaern, forming a basic plan spat near the child, aiming carefully &quot;Is that creature a High Elf?&quot; he said, in a mean tone &quot;Why is such a pathetic creature allowed within these walls?&quot;<br><br>Quite surprised the General looked at him, temporarily distracted &quot;Tell me human, you despise them too?&quot;<br><br>&quot;Of course&quot; Dlaern replied, trying to keep up his mean appearance &quot;One of her wretched kind did this to me&quot; he pointed at the eyepatch upon his face &quot;What do you want for that thing? I will pay whatever you ask to be able to cause pain to such a small one would bring great satisfaction&quot;<br><br>The General, seemingly believing his act replied &quot;For this one? I ask one hundred platinum pieces&quot;<br><br>&quot;Do you jest?&quot; Dlaern thought for a moment and tried too look like he was looking at the child &quot;I will pay no more than twenty, she is near death already, you have done quite a job&quot;<br><br>&quot;Fifty or she stays here&quot;<br><br>&quot;Very well&quot; Dlaern called over one of the bankers, and then gave a small bag of coins to the General. Turning to the small child, &quot;Come with me, you are mine now&quot;<br><br>He took the girl to a small alcove near the water against the great wall, out of sight of the Guards &quot;Are you alright small one?&quot; he asked, changing his voice to be as gentle as possible. She cringed away as he reached for her<br><br>&quot;Please, do not be afraid, I only want to help&quot; She was badly hurt, cuts and bruises covered most of her body, he took out a roll of bandages and showed them to her, tearing off one he soaked it ad gently took her arm, noticing a strange ring upon her finger, but dismissing it for the moment &quot;This may sting a little&quot; <br><br>He bound the wounds as best he could, but he knew she would require the help of a person with healing magics. The odds of finding such a person would be hard here, and what to do with her when she was well?<br><br>Then the idea struck him, Tanthian's orphanage, he had been there before, even if she could not take her she might be able to help a little. But how to get there? without magical aid the best way would be to get upon the boat sailing for the Oasis.<br><br>He removed his cloak and put it on the child, he picked her up in his arms despite her objections and walked to the docks, he could see the Bloated Belly in the distance sailing closer so he increased his pace<br><br>He covered up her head so not to get the attention of the Dragoon or the Herald as he past. Climbing aboard the boat he set her down in a more secluded part of the boat and sat with her to wait out the trip<br><br>**************************<br><br>After sneaking past the Ogres to get upon the raft, and then past the numerous creatures in the Deserts of Ro and the Oasis he made it to the city of Freeport, luckily the girl had fallen asleep on the boat so she was easier to carry, <br><br>He did not trust the Freeport Militia, and they were a little wary of him since he had been seen aiding Nasmith in killing a Guard a while back he decided to use the sewer system to travel, passing through the secret wall and through the tunnels to the Western Gate then onto the northern realm. Appearing near the Office of Landholders he made his way to the Jaded Jaguar.<br><br>He paid the owner for rental of a room and climbed the stairs, the child getting quite heavy now was laid on the bed to rest, Dlaern sitting in the corner, meditating to regain his strength<br><br>A few hours later Dlaern had fallen asleep, but was awoken by his amulet, a female voice he knew very well was greeting the Knights, activating his own he spoke back &quot;Good Morning my love, how are you today?&quot;<br><br>Thinking of his current problem he got an idea, focusing his thoughts to speak to only Wizzina he explained the situation, &quot;Wizzina, I ask for your help, could you use your magics to aid my travels?&quot;<br><br>&quot;Of course Dlaern, I shall teleport myself to the Northern Deserts of Ro and meet you as soon as possible&quot;<br><br>Using the time for her arrival he checked upon the small child, she was still fast asleep &quot;I wonder what her name is?&quot; he thought aloud &quot;I can't very well call her little one&quot;<br><br>She stirred and opened her eyes, as she saw Dlaern again she instantly cowered back to the corner, covering herself from harm<br><br>&quot;Please don't, I won't hurt you,&quot; he placed his weapons upon the table and walked away from them &quot;see, I just want to help, what is your name?&quot;<br><br>Fear in her eyes she said nothing just looked at him, shaking visibly he reached into his bag and took out a ration, he held it out to her &quot;Are you hungry?&quot; he put it down next to her and backed off, she picked it up and ate it quickly, seeming like she hadn't eaten for days, which was quite likely in reality<br><br>Reaching back into the bag he took out a flask of water and held that out, this time she moved forward quickly, grabbing the bottle and jumping back, Dlaern chuckled &quot;Well, that's improvement I guess, do you want to tell me your name now?&quot;<br><br>She still said nothing, a little less fear showed though. Suddenly there was a knock on the door, the girl dove under the covers, shaking. Dlaern stood up took his baton and opened the door a little.<br><br>Upon seeing who it was he opened the door and invited her in, giving her a soft kiss on the cheek, he said &quot;Wizzina this is the girl, she seems very cautious around strangers, perhaps she'll be more comfortable around you&quot;<br><br>He walked over to the bed &quot;Don't be frightened, this is Wizzina, she is here to help you too&quot; the girl slowly peeked out from under the covers and instantly dove back under<br><br>he spoke quietly to Wizzina, &quot;Don't be offended, she is very meek, she seems to have been treated really badly at the outpost&quot; she nodded in reply &quot;Could we depart soon?&quot;<br><br>she replied in the same hushed tone &quot;Yes, i memorized the spell before I arrived, I think she can be taken from where she is, but unless you can get her out from under there the sheet is coming with us&quot;<br><br>Dlaern chuckled and placed a few coins on the table that should cover a new sheet, I don't think we'll be getting her out soon&quot;<br><br>**********************<br><br>Wizzina took the trio to the spires in the Northern Planes of Karanas, Dlaern said farewell and kissed her &quot;I shall see you soon i hope, we still have much to discuss&quot;<br><br>Once she left the little girl peeked out from the sheet, and looked at Dlaern &quot;Don't worry, we are safe, I'm taking you to meet a very nice lady who will make you feel better&quot; he knelt close, &quot;Do you want to walk with me or should I carry you?&quot;<br><br>She stood up and walked a little closer, Dlaern lifted her and started his trek, he kept to the great river to avoid confrontations and made his way across the Great Plains<br><br>***********************<br><br>It was near nightfall by time Dlaern caught sight of the building, he hoped someone was in and his hopes were answered when he knocked upon the door to have Tanthian herself answer<br><br>&quot;M'Lady, this child needs medical attention, please&quot; she let them in and he carried her to a chair, Tanthian used her magic to cure some of the wounds<br><br>They used a spare bed to let the girl sleep while Dlaern told the tale to Tanthian, &quot;I did not know where else to go&quot; he looked at her, &quot;I ask if you have a spare place for her, I would willingly pay for her accomedation&quot;<br><br>&quot;It is quite late, I ask that you think about my question overnight and give me your answer in the morn?&quot;<br><br>She nodded in reply, &quot;Do you require a room also?&quot;<br><br>&quot;I do not believe so, I will make my camp outside, I believe that would be more convient&quot;<br><br>***************************<br><br>The next day Tanthian, awoken by the sounds of fighting from outside rushed to the door, as she opened the door prepared to face whoever was attacking she smiled at the sight she saw,<br><br>Young Delahr was the attacker as he swung his punches and kicks at Dlaern. Dlaern was able to dodge or block most of the attacks but was distracted by Tanthian, turning his head he said &quot;I hope we did not wake you, its seems Delahr found out I was here, he has been trying to learn new attacks all morning&quot;<br><br>Suddenly Delahr using Dlaern's distraction to his advantage performed a round kick to Dlaerns flank, catching him off balance again and flooring him for the second time<br><br>Breathing heavily and laughing he slowly got back up &quot;Well, at least i can blame that one on you M'Lady&quot; he beamed a smile, then he bowed before Tanthian &quot;May i ask your decision upon the girl?&quot; <br><br><br>All through the night, Tanthian kept checking on the small girl sleeping. There were times she cried out, and it broke Tanthian's poor soft heart. She touched her softly, smoothing fine strands of long hair from her round young face.<br><br>It just didn't make sense how anyone could harm young children like that... she rubbed her growing belly protectively, angered and outraged.<br><br>When morning finally came, she awoke after a couple hours of sleep, meeting Dlaern in the yard. She watched with amusement, seeing him sparring with the young boy, and glad for the mentorship he offered the child.<br><br>&quot;Dlaern, it is my life's calling to care for children. Of course she can stay here.... for as long as it takes. She is just Ziah's age, and Ziah is studying magic in Felwithe now. Perhaps I will send this child there, and they can room together... Of course, she is in no emotional or physical condition for that.&quot;<br><br>She motioned for him to follow her, and they went into the small building when the child rested. She had just awoken, and Tanthian knelt beside her bed, turning tender and kind eyes on her.<br><br>&quot;Hello, sweet. My name is Tanthian. I'm the mistress of this place, and I call it the Ivy Cradle. There are lots of children who live here with me and they learn all sorts of things, and I keep them very safe.&quot; She smiles gently, making sure the girl is following her words before she continues. &quot;Can you tell me your name, and maybe where you come from and things like that? I want to help you as much as I can, and talking a little is the beginning of that...&quot;<br><br>She studied the little girl very carefully, smiling gently, and keeping a respectful distance, and listened closely, nodding and prompting her to continue... <br><br><br>Having not yet met Tanthian, Drexsys made her way to her. She had heard of her condition and wished to pass the blessings of Tunare on to her. Her husband had recently visited the Keep and left his message of kinship, she felt welcome and wished to meet them both.<br>She entered the room with Tanthian and gasped at the condition of the small high elf. Covering her mouth, she turned away, a tear burning hot and bright in the corner of her eye.<br>&quot;Forgive me, Mistress, I shall await you outside.&quot; <br><br>My treasures do not clink together or glitter; They gleam in the sun and neigh in the night<br><br><br>After unsuccessfully attempting to coax the child to speak, Tanthian gave up for the day, deciding the girl had had enough. She did her very best to keep herself together, and approach with gentle kindness, but the child was traumatized far worse than any that had come to the Cradle, except perhaps Ziah.<br><br>Speaking in elvish, Tanthian murmured quietly to the child, &quot;You know, dear one, that you can take all the time you need to get settled and comfortable. I will be making sure food gets brought to you that is good to eat, and that you have a place all of your own to stay. I will come back a little later with a girl just about your age who can stay with you and keep you company.&quot;<br><br>Slowly making her way out of the building she met Drexsys outside.<br><br>&quot;Hail Lady Drexsys, and well met again. I believe we saw each other at the Right of Justice recently. Allow me to formally introduce myself. I am Tanthian Faetyrin, mistress of this humble habitué. Come into the office and sit for tea with me.&quot;<br><br>She walks to one of the buildings, and sits with Drexsys, offering tea and crunchy cookies. She smiles gently at the elf.<br><br>&quot;You saw an unfortunate thing, Lady Drexsys. Perhaps you did not fully understand the types of children we take in here... most of them would die without our care. Some have suffered grievously... others were simply abandoned, as if that somehow is more acceptably than beating and burning your own child.&quot; Her eyes glitter with deep outrage at the things she'd seen since she opened the Cradle's doors.<br><br>&quot;That young child recently came to us, and I fear it will take many weeks before she has come around enough even to stay in the regular dormitory.... &quot; she trails off, carefully looking over the notations that Chrislin had made about another child and etching a response, and then returns her gaze to Drexsys.<br><br>&quot;So, my lady, what brings you here to this sanctuary? Is there something I can do for you?&quot; <br><br><br>The girl was still quite hurt, but her condition had improved considerably, he had rarely seen those so hurt and yet still alive, her improved state was still quite upsetting to see, <br><br>Tanthian led Dlaern to the room, trying her best to get the small child to speak was having little response, in fact she seemed a little afraid of Tanthian. Dlaern was confused, she has cringed away from Wizzina and now seemed to be trying to protect herself from Tanthian.<br><br>It was about then when Lady Drexsys arrived, she retreated quickly, a few moments later Tanthian spoke a little Elvish and followed Drexsys out.<br><br>&quot;Well, how are you today then?&quot; he spoke gently to the Child &quot;Is there anything we can call you?&quot;<br><br>She simply looked at him, &quot;Are you hungry?&quot; he searched through his bag for some food, he found a small ration and held it out to her, reaching out slowly she took the ration and put it down next to her &quot;Saving it for later then&quot;<br><br>Looking at her hand as she took the ration he noticed the ring again, he could see nothing special about it but it might tell him something<br><br>&quot;Those two ladies who were here, they won't hurt you, don't be afraid&quot; he sighed &quot;You will be safe here, okay&quot;<br><br>He walked out and met the two ladies, he bowed before them &quot;When you are finished could I have a quick word with you Lady Tanthian?&quot;<br><br>She nodded and he left quietly, he waited outside and meditated, waiting for either the Ladies or Delahr to attack again. <br><br><br>It had been some time since Volairn had been back to the Cradle, and he felt long overdue for a visit. Knowing his wife was there may also have had something to do with its inexorable call to him. They had so much to talk about in those short weeks. Volairn had discovered, met and already grown to love a daughter--young Katharyn--born from a liaison out of wedlock over twenty years ago. Tanthian herself was noticeably pregnant now, and he had a hard time pulling himself away longer than a few days; already it had been twelve long days.<br><br>As Opla realized where they were, he picked up the pace and would not be slowed by the reigns. Volairn laughed as Opla swept into a canter when the buildings of the Ivy Cradle rose into view from the grasslands of the Karanas. Volairn imagined Opla was excited for the honey oats in the stable there, or maybe to see Feena, Tanthian's mare. Whatever the reason, he was docile and as amiable to the children of the Cradle as any horse could be.<br><br>And the children, they could hear him coming a mile away and waited like enemy infantry setting their pikes against a charge. They would rush out of the buildings, cheering and shouting, and this time was no different.<br><br>As the morning sun warmed the Karanas, Volairn finally convinced Opla to stop, and hopped out of the saddle to receive the rush of children. They would have to work for it today, Volairn told himself, nodding with a mischievous grin. <br><br>And like ants their assault prevailed. In a wave of cheers and hugs they took him to the ground, and in time he was laughing and making a half hearted attempt to fend off the attack. Finally he shouted happily, &quot;I yield, brave knights, I yield.&quot;<br><br>And with that, the next ritual began. He stood up, panting for breath, but making no effort to dust himself off. He smiled at the throng of children, and reached into Opla's saddle bag, pulling out the treats he always brought them. This time, Fur Foot Taffee, a sweet from Rivervale that was sure to keep them chewing all the way until lunch time.<br><br>Finally, having thoroughly disrupted the children's morning routines, and knowing he would have to answer for his sins of candy in the morning, he looked around for his wife. Normally she would be in his arms by now. He was about to ask one of the elder children where she was when he saw Dlaern standing from his meditative pose.<br><br>&quot;Dlaern!&quot; Volairn smiled and waved. &quot;What a pleasant surprise!&quot;<br><br>He wondered if his curiosity showed as he offered the monk a piece of Fur Foot Taffee. <br><br><br>Dlaern sat quietly, meditating, when a noise can be heard in the distance, opening his eye slowly he looked to see a man on a horse approaching, as it slowed to a halt the rider dismounted and was quickly assaulted by most of the children<br><br>Considering whether to assist the man or the children was quickly decided as the mans voice yelled in submission, as he rose Dlaern recognized him as Lord Volairn,<br><br>He searched his bag for something and brought out a small bag, distributing the contents to the children Dlaern slowly got up<br><br>bowing in response to Volairn greeting &quot;Hail Lord Vol, how are you?&quot;<br><br>&quot;Quite well, where is my wife hiding?&quot;<br><br>Dlaern chuckled softly &quot;Lady Tanthian is with Lady Drexsys inside, I presume she will be out shortly, this will be the second time she would come out due to a disturbance, myself and Delahr woke her a little early this morning&quot;<br><br>Volairn nodded and laughed, &quot;So what brings you here?&quot;<br><br>Dlaern became more serious, &quot;Unfortunately I am not here for pleasure&quot; Dlaern recited the tale to Volairn, a few minutes later he finished, he got a faint idea &quot;Lord Vol? do you still have a few candies spare?&quot; <br><br><br>&quot;Well, I will let her finish her business with Lady Drexsys.&quot; Volairn nods. &quot;She will find me easy enough.&quot;<br><br>Volairn had listened patiently to Dlaern's story, a quiet rage brewing within as he heard of the young girl's plight.<br><br>He pasted on his grin again, for the sake of the children nearby, not wanting to pass on his emotion to them. The last thing these troubled children needed was another worry.<br><br>&quot;Here, Dlaern.&quot; Volairn hands a small leather pouch. &quot;This is the last of the sweets. I think I have some idea of what you have in mind. I will wait here though. I worry my presence might frighten the poor dear.&quot;<br><br>With that Volairn leads Opla to the stable to brush him down, water, and feed him. As eager as he was to see his wife, he would let her finish her dealings, and Opla needed a good combing anyway. He hummed a sailor's tune as he worked, but still the rage churned within... <br><br><br>&quot;Thank you Lord Vol&quot; he bowed before Volairn and walked back to see the girl, <br><br>Slowly entering the room, he kept a reasonable distance, places his weapons on the table slowly &quot;Hi, are you okay?&quot; he asked quietly, I have a little treat for you, they are from Lord Volairn, he doesn't want to scare you but you will meet him eventually&quot;<br><br>He walked over slowly, holding the small pouch and taking a small sweet from it, holding it out to her &quot;I don't suppose you want to tell me your name?&quot; she reached out for the sweet, taking it from Dlaern &quot;Well, we can't just call you little one can we?&quot;<br><br>She put the sweet in her mouth, slowly sucking on it a small smile started to show, &quot;You like that don't you?&quot; the girl slowly moved her head in a nod<br><br>&quot;That's improvement I suppose&quot; he grinned at her &quot;Small steps, would you like another of Vol's sweets?&quot; she nodded again, only slight movements but noticeable, Dlaern took out another sweet and handed it to the girl<br><br>She was definately making improvements, but Dlaern knew it might take a while, and a lot more sweets, he would have to ask Volairn where he got them.<br><br><br>Drexsys regained her composure and managed a smile at Tanthian, and gladly accepted the tea, which had a rich, sweet flavor. She smoothed her dress with her hands and took another long sip, enjoying the taste. Tanthian, it seemed, was good at many things.<br>&quot;I have heard much about you, Mistress Tanthian, I had hoped to meet you.&quot; Drexsys glanced at her stomach, which had started to swell visibly, and smiled a genuine smile.<br>&quot;one such as yourself will be wonderful mother,&quot; she continued,&quot; you've obviously done much with the children here. I can hear them yelling about something outside and they are quite happy.&quot; She paused, listening to the commotion going on outside.<br>&quot;Where are my manners?&quot; Drexsys stood up hastily, suddenly remembering that she hadn't even bothered to introduce herself yet.<br>&quot;I am Drexsys Xinnae, wife of Stingerfx Xin, citizen of the Jaded Dragons. Volairn left a message in our keep and I wanted to thank him and yourself. We always need friendships and allies, and now moreso than ever.&quot;<br>Tanthian chuckled at the high elf, knowing how pained children tended to cause absentmindedness in others.<br>&quot;Shall we see what's going on outside?&quot; Tanthian asked.<br>&quot;Certainly,&quot; said Drexsys, &quot;I'm sure Firegod has gotten himself into trouble again. I heard another horse ride up and haven't heard him, so I'm sure there is mischief brewing. Just one question, though, what happened to that child and where did she come from?&quot;<br>Tanthian told her all she knew and put an arm around her shoulder as they walked out. <br><br><br>&quot;There is only so much that we can do in a short time, Lady Drexsys... that child... well... we shall see in time. But I have hope for ALL children. You know, they certainly have a beautiful way of bouncing back, even from knocks that would emotionally cripple an adult. Gosh...&quot; she says, gazing off with a dreamy-eyed smile, &quot;they are a blessing, a marvel, and a daily inspiration for me. I love them, and believe in them all.&quot;<br><br>Peering outside, with her guest, she saw her husband, and beamed a gleaming white-toothed smile at him. She sat heavily on the ground, tickling one of the boys mercilessly, herself laughing like a maniac, momentarily forgetting her company. She seemed far more at home holding the small boy than anywhere else, and her glee filled her face.<br><br>Looking up at Volairn and Lady Drexsys, still smiling, she spoke.<br><br>&quot;I am so honored that you would come all this way simply to offer your congratulations! Gracious! It isn't often that people make the trek out here to West Karana! Is there anything else you wanted, or were you perhaps curious about the work we conduct here?&quot;<br><br>She paused, then got a bright smight, signaling them to stay put, and she raced off to a building. Coming back quickly, beaming proudly, she held a tiny chubby baby cradled in her arms. The baby slept, still too young to do much else.<br><br>&quot;This is a baby that was left here... her father left a note saying that he couldn't care for the girl, and her mother had died in labor. It has only been a few days... and I haven't named her yet!&quot;<br><br>She smiled, perhaps a bit sadly, at Lady Drexsys, and then handed her the tiny child. <br><br>&quot;What do you think we should call her?&quot; <br><br><br>Drexsys gasped, not quite sure what to say. It was indeed an honored request from her newfound friend, and she was very pleased. She held out her arms to hold the child, and Tanthian carefully handed the little lady to her. Drexsys touched the tiny, soft forehead and stroked her eyes, and the baby gurgled in her sleep. She looked at Volairn and Tanthian thoughtfully, and thought of all the beautiful elven words she knew. A wizard very rarely has time to think upon such things, but today, that was all there was, this baby and the bright, happy children in West Karana. She kissed the dimpled cheek of the child gently, and the baby stirred, turning in her arms. Drexsys smiled and knew the words she was searching for. <br>&quot;Should I choose, I would call the child Araya 'Tu, or Tunare's Gift in Koada D'al,&quot; She said softly. &quot;She is a pure child, and shall someday do great things.&quot;<br>A small murmur came from the doorway, and the group turned to see the small Elven child standing there, watching them. She turned quickly and retreated when the attention rested upon her, not wanting to be seen.<br>&quot;She will come round,&quot; Volairn said with a loving look at his wife, &quot;she is magic with them.&quot; He turned to Drexsys and said, &quot;my Lady, have you met Dlaern?&quot;<br>&quot;Why, no, my apologies, sir, very pleased to meet you.&quot; <br><br><br>Tanthian giggled with joy.<br><br>&quot;Araya'Tu. I love it!&quot; she nods carefully. &quot;Hence she shall be called!&quot;<br><br>She watched Drexsys carefully, seeing her interact with the baby, and enjoying her enjoying the tiny child. She felt a smile grace her face as she watched the High Elf and the child, framed with the backdrop of the big Karana sky.<br><br>&quot;So, interested in teaching wizardry classes here?&quot;<br><br>Tanthian laughed, long and loud, so grateful for the company... but her mind ever churning and planning... carefully considering what was best for he young elven girl, who was so wounded inside, and out. <br><br><br>Drexsys raised an eyebrow at Tanthian and beamed a bright smile. <br>&quot;You are quick to seize opportunity,&quot; she chuckled. &quot;I would be most honored.&quot;<br>Tanthian grinned back, quite pleased with herself.<br>Araya gurgled again and curled up tigher against Drexsys and she couldn't have been happier.<br>A rumble caught her attention and Drexsys turned to see Firegod, the great dark elven beast, the scarred one, the creature dark as night, laying on the ground getting his ears pulled and his tail braided. He appeared to be enjoying himself immensely.<br>The group laughed.<br>&quot;I think I shall journey here often,&quot; Drexsys said. &quot;I can teach jewelcraft, as well. Which children have shown an interest in magic? Maybe you can introduce me?&quot; <br><br><br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>~~My treasures do not clink together or glitter; they gleam in the sun and neigh in the night~~</td></tr>
