	   <tr><td colspan=2><br>The breeze was cool, quite refreshing after the confines of Blackburrow. Drexsys was quite pleased, the signing was done, the alliance was now official . . . yet she sensed something wasn't right. <br><br>She walked slowly away from the dungeon and then, from within the small hut a Tier'Dal step towards the blazing fire. Seeing their kind was uncommon and a bit unnerving, but not that unusual, she continued but she strayed a little off course towards the tree to avoid him.<br><br>The feeling began to increase as yet another Tier'Dal emerged from behind the tree, <br><br>&quot;You will be coming with us Drexsys&quot; said the first from behind her, she turned to face him but instead she saw three, and another two appeared behind her, &quot;Resistance is pointless, you don't stand a chance&quot;<br><br>&quot;I don't think so&quot; she replied, her fingers sparkling with energy, striking the first Dark Elf with an amazing thunderbolt, sending him flying back. With her attackers stunned for a moment she began to cast a quick area effect spell, to give her some time to escape<br><br>&quot;Incompetent foolss&quot; she heard from above, distracting her from her casting. She looked up but nothing was there, but she heard a small thud behind her where yet another attacker landed, she turned to face the new person but as she did her casting was interrupted by the shock of what she saw &quot;. . . Coranax&quot; she stammered<br><br>He muttered two words quietly so only Drexsys could hear, then swung his Knobbed Warclub striking the High Elf across the side of her head, rendering her unconscious instantly. Meanwhile the wounded Dark Elf slowly got up and drew his sword and walked towards the unconscious body.<br><br>&quot;What are you doing?&quot; asked one of the Troopers<br><br>&quot;I am going to make her regret fighting back&quot; replied the injured Captain<br><br>&quot;No you are not!&quot; snarled Coranax, staring directly at the Captain<br><br>&quot;But she tried to kill me sir&quot; he replied, anger simmering within him &quot;I want to make her pay for what she did to me&quot;<br><br>&quot;Sshe tried to kill you?&quot; he replied with a small grin, suddenly turning to a snarl &quot;Let me finish the job&quot; he blasted the already wounded Tier'Dal with the Spirits of Frost, he leapt through the air, drawing his spear from his back and driving it into the black heart, destroying the last beat of life within the small body &quot;No-one iss to harm her ass long ass I am breathing, sshe iss no good to uss dead, Understood?&quot;<br><br>The small group of Dark Elves muttered for a moment but replied in union &quot;Yes Sir&quot;<br><br>The Iksar walked up to the seemingly lifeless body, and picked up up with the minimal of ease, placing her on his shoulder &quot;Letss go&quot;<br><br><br>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>Gurnan is awakened by a loud rapping on the door of his tavern room. His thinking is sluggish (moreso than usual) from heavy drink the night before.<br><br>&quot;what is it?&quot; he mumbles<br><br>Again the rapping continues, louder this time.<br><br>&quot;WHAT?&quot; he mutters louder himself.<br><br>The rapping, now a loud crashing, accompanied by a loud shout &quot;SIR! SIR! WE HAVE AN URGENT MESSAGE FOR YOU, IT'S FROM YOUR KEEP!&quot;<br><br>The warrior feels a deep sense of shock, had Beltzerr gone AWOL again? or had the shadows returned to haunt them?<br><br>He looks at the gnomish wrist-worn-time-teller, that had been a gift from tiny Zarquon, the gnome who liked strong drink and stood up to him so long ago. it is nearly Sunday, the alliance would now be finalized, maybe it was a notice of this for him.<br><br>&quot;I'll be out in a sec, ma friend!&quot; shouts the Barbarian, now wide awake &quot;jus' lemme get decent&quot;<br><br>He throws his leather under tunic on hurridly, followed by his kilt before opening the door.<br><br><br>&quot;what be the fuss then laddie!&quot;<br><br>&quot;sir, I don't know, it was delivered by a bard with many such notes, he said to read it fast and 'get his stinking hide to the keep ASAP'&quot;<br><br>&quot;that's nice, sounds like Ren to me though, never did like me scent much, dang pretty-boy bard&quot;<br><br>He opens the note, certain that it was an exaggeration of import.<br><br>Reading it, his face loses the happy red sheen that was his norm. <br>&quot;$&amp;@#&quot;<br><br>Thunderstruck, Gurnan races back to his bedside, packs his few belongings into bags, dons his armor and storms out of the building, only leaving money as an afterthought. <br><br>------------------------<br><br>Drexsys kidnapped, by party or parties unknown at this time. He felt sorry for the perpetrators, Stinger would skin them alive when he found them!<br><br>Another Iksar watches as Gurnan dashes out of the Keep. She still carries the wounds of a dragon that didn't even exist, and grimaces as she bandages her arm. She steps from the shadows to stop Gurnan, and is instantaneously bowled over by the hulking barbarian. Angrily, she roots him to the ground, pulls herself up, and stalks over to him.<br>&quot;Damned lizard!&quot; he snaps. &quot;what's your problem? no time, no time!&quot;<br>Drexonae stops, a bit perplexed, and hisses, &quot;what isss the problem, barbarian? I ssshall ssskin you alive ssshould you run me over like that again.&quot;<br>Gurnan's face regains its color and continues to a bright purple color.<br>&quot;It's Drexsys, you stupid lizard, she's been taken!&quot;<br>At that the root breaks, and Gurnan is gone, moving as fast as his bulk allows. <br>Drexonae falls to the ground, stunned. She recalls, for a moment, the kindness shown to her by the Elf and an anger unlike any she has ever felt takes control of her, sending her seething into a furious fit. She drops the bandages and sprints to the Keep, and takes her Harpoon in claw. With the fury of a demon she sharpens it to a painfully sharp point, holds it above her hand, and listens as its howl becomes clearer, louder. She practices a few thrusts with every muscle in her body taut as wire, then takes off after Gurnan, hoping to catch him. <br><br><br>Dramius rushes through Shadows hunting down the Druids that live in the 29th circle and Druids of higher Circles. As soon as the word of Hate reached her ears she ran twice as fast as she would have with any thing to increase my speed. Anything in her way was either destroyed by the wave of hate in front of her or her channeled anger destroyed them.<br>She never knew her hate to be So strong.<br><br><br>Returning from the War of Sebilis, Damienn was eager to see his fellow clansmen and show off his Fungi tunic he ripped from the corpse of the dead king. As sweet as victory was, Damienn was more excited to almost be home. <br><br>Only a few miles from the keep he saw what looked like a bear running towards him down the trail. As it grew near he began to recognize it was Gurnan the Barbarian a fellow clansmen. &quot;Hail&quot; shouted Damien in an excited voice, knowing that if there be a man to drink with it would be Gurnan. <br><br>&quot;Oh thank the Gods' its you Damienn&quot; says Gurnan as he stops running and leans against a tree grasping for breath. Is there a free ale sale going on chuckled Damienn, I don't remember the last time I seen a man run so hard. <br><br>&quot;NO&quot; shouted Gurnan, &quot;it's Drexsys&quot; as he tries to catch his breath. Oh, oh says Damienn, don't tell me she is chasing you, did you call her shorty again? <br><br>If that were only the case says Gurnan. I have received word that Drexsys has been kidnapped. WHAT!! Shouts Damienn who would dare!! We are unsure, I just received word myself says Gurnan. <br><br>As his once excited voice turns to a dark angered tune, his hands begin to glow red like flames of 