me of a candle, and set it to burn, dropping it into the library fireplace to be completely consumed. She then took quill and parchment in hand, and wrote a quick note:<br><br>&quot;Sivina:<br><br>Thank you for the news. Please continue to observe and send word with more developments.<br><br>Deva.&quot;<br><br>She affixed her own seal to the letter and placed it on the tray for Eldrim to pick up, later. She would keep tabs on the situation. But in the meantime...<br><br>With a heavy sigh she dropped back into her chair and resumed her reading, while her stew got cold.<br><br><br>In a small forest Dlaern is quietly meditating yet again, that's the problem with being spiritual rather than holy. Being agnostic does have its disadvantages (in the words of a great philosopher 'they cant make me believe in them just by smiting me')<br><br>Just then his peaceful moment is interrupted by a hulking Barbarian smashing his way through the forest. Gurnan stops just a few feet from the monk and leans up against a tree breathing heavily &quot;Must get there,&quot; he mutters &quot;then smash the damn thing who took lady Drexsys&quot;<br><br>&quot;Excuse me&quot; pips up the little monk &quot;May I ask where you are going in such a hurry&quot;<br><br>He spins and looks down at the human &quot;Me going to Blackburrow, our leaders missus has gone missing, we's thinkin she been taken&quot;<br><br>&quot;Can I help?&quot; he inquires<br><br>&quot;if youse can keep up&quot; grunts Gurnan, ready to run again. he starts running again headed for Blackburrow, the little monk using his agility manages to keep up whilst dodging the multiple branches being thrown back<br><br>**************<br><br>Outside the dungeon of Blackburrow there is a gathering of the Jaded dragon, searching for clues for Drexsys' kidnappers<br><br>&quot;Me here where Stingerfx? and wot we know at the moment?&quot;<br><br>&quot;Not much&quot; pips up a tiny Gnome, &quot;we can't seem to fi