s she has been enchanted or poisoned. She quickly and quietly unties her feet and with the agility of a cat, she mounts the beast and squeezes his side. <br>The dark horse happily obliges, and the two are off, walking quietly to slip out of the camp into the predawn. Once they are clear, the horse needs no urging, he runs as if Cazic Thule himself is on his tail.<br>Together, the vanish into the hills, Drexsys hardly breathing, hoping to get home before she is caught. <br><br>Coranax returns to the encampment, &quot;One more little project before we leave I think&quot; he mutters, &quot;But first, Drexsys&quot;<br><br>He walks through the sleeping Elves, and then he notices a elf missing, Drexsys &quot;MORONSS&quot; he roars, &quot;YOU LET HER GET AWAY!&quot;<br><br>The yelling Iksar wakes the Elves with a start, they look around, terrified of what was going to happen<br><br>Coranax grabs the nearest Tier'Dal, lifts him off the floor and throws him through the air into another one, &quot;WHAT ARE YOU SSTILL DOING HERE? FIND HER NOW!&quot;<br><br>They scamper off quickly, no real idea of where they are going, but they just know if they don't find her they are all dead. <br><br>&quot;They have no chance, I'll get her later, sshe will sstill be drowsy from the potion, and sshe sshouldnt know where sshe iss to start, I hope sshe doesnt find that amulet though itss the only thing preventing her from using her sspellss now&quot; mutters Coranax &quot;But I have another to deal with now&quot;<br><br>**********************<br><br>Drexonae is scanning the area for Coranax's scent, trying to assist the Dragons to find Drexsys, suddenly she picks up the scent, and it's fresh and quite strong<br><br>&quot;Greetingss, looking for me?&quot; asks Coranax<br><br>She jumps and bares her teeth, &quot;where isss Drexssysss traitor?&quot;<br><br>&quot;You will know, after you make a decision&quot;<br><br>&quot;Which iss?&quot;<br><br>&quot;Where your loyalti