un when the numbers are more even. Besides right now I must find a way to smooth things over with Coranax, he is not going to be very pleased to see me again. Perhaps a gift to show my dedication to his cause&quot; <br>Khandura then looks at the group and singles out a young gnome huffing and puffing bent over and holding his knees. Khandura grins evilly, &quot;ahhh yes I wonder when was the last time Lord Coranax has had a taste of tender Gnome flesh?&quot;<br>As Khandura starts his way toward the gnome, who has fallen behind from exhaustion, out of the corner of his eye he catches a glimpse of one of the barbarians looking his way yet has not yet figured out what he was looking at. Khandura stops frozen in his tracks perhaps Lord Coranax's gift shall have to wait&quot; then without barely moving a finger Khandura casts his shadow step spell to move him to a safe enough distance from the group to make his exit into the underground through an opening which looks like a large rabbit hole.<br>Khandura<br>Break the bones and the body shall heal<br>Break the spirit and the body shall die <br><br><br>Thaylon sits still in wolf form his tongue lolling to a side panting heavily. He howls the howl of a sad wolf who has lost one of the pack. The sound echoes and in the distance others pick up his mournful cry till just his can be heard. He finally collapses and falls to his side.<br>He waits for the pack to start moving again knowing this time the trail has grown cold. Trying to remember what he saw on the other side of the portal that would leave a clue but his mind can't yet form the image. H e hopes someone saw the image before they vanished and recognized the terrain. He is to tired to offer the suggestion. He curls upon the ground and waits for stingers lead. His anger seething to new crescendos. Images of Iksar being shredded dance through his head. Alas he focuses on the problem. Realizing all he can do is wait. <br><br>&quot;Did anyone else see that?&quot; wheezes the now exhausted Zarquon<br>&quot;I swear i saw someone vanish over there!&quot;<br><br>&quot;Ok little fella, now explain to me, how can you SEE someone vanish eh?&quot; Gurnan asks, making sure the whole group can hear him<br>&quot;I'm telling you, someone was there&quot; He points up to the hillside &quot;they were right there&quot; now frustrated at the Barbarian's sarcasm he goes to Kulden, but he, like everyone else, is too upset by the near rescue of Drexsys and just sits there staring at where the dark elf's portal had been.<br><br>&quot;Well.&quot; Zarquon says, almost to himself &quot;Its times like this I wish I'd taken up brewing instead of tinkering&quot; Then he lays on the grass and stares at the morning clouds. <br><br><br>&quot;Oi Boss&quot; shouts Gurnan, &quot;I found a Inkie while I was looking for Lady Drexsys, I . . . err asked him a few questions and found out some nice stuff&quot;<br><br>The tired Stingerfx perked up at this news &quot;What did you find Gurnan?&quot;<br><br>&quot;He said there a small outpost where they taking Drexsys, he told me where it was too&quot;<br><br>&quot;Well, what are we waiting for&quot; he replied, shouting to the others &quot;Spread the word, we have a lead to Drexsys&quot;<br><br>********************<br><br>A quite large band of Dragons and a few Candiria Knights turned were waiting silently looking upon the outpost, it was as told quite small, and yet it was one of the most fortified structures they had even seen <br><br>&quot;This isn't going to be easy&quot; muttered Zarquon &quot;And we don't even know if she's in there&quot;<br><br>&quot;I may be able to find out I think&quot; hissed Drexonae &quot;Coranax approached me and asked me to join hisss ssside, I may be able to bluff my way to dissscover if ssshe isss there&quot;<br><br>&quot;That would be dangerous&quot; commented Stingerfx<br><br>&quot;Yeah send the lizard&quot; muttered Goggwin, but he shrunk away once she replied with a scowl<br><br>&quot;I want to rescue Drexssysss, if thisss will do it I will go&quot; she slipped away and walk boldly up to the door being watched carefully just in case. &quot;I want to talk to Coranax, isss he here?&quot; she snarled<br><br>&quot;Urgh . . . (what do we do?)&quot;<br><br>&quot;(It knows Coranax, let her in, I don't want to get in trouble)&quot;<br><br>&quot;Yes he's here, guarding the hostage until the master arrives&quot;<br><br>[confirmation, ssshe'sss here] she thinks to herself<br><br>She made it look like she was entering but she managed to sip past and return to the hillside and she reported her findings<br><br>&quot;Let's get her out then&quot; roared Stingerfx, the small band charged at the door, knocking the two guards easily aside and entering to engage in a bloody battle with the multiple Elves, Ogres and Trolls<br><br>********************<br><br>&quot;I am here now&quot; said Coranax &quot;Why thiss place, there iss no need for all thiss ssecurity&quot;<br><br>&quot;The master is due, there is not enough security to protect him&quot;<br><br>&quot;What?&quot; he roared &quot;Why wass I not informed?&quot;<br><br>&quot;He didn't think it was relative&quot;<br><br>[not good] thought Coranax, he walked to Drexsys in her cell, he ordered the guards away, woke her up and quietly gave her a message. He dragged her out from the cell to the main chamber, &quot;The master will be here ssoon, he will choose your fate Ssoftskin&quot;<br><br><br>********************<br><br>The combined forces of the two guild are battling there way through hall after hall, into each room with no luck, many a foes have fallen to the blades, daggers, and bolts of magic. The corpses fill the fort, blood from both sides flow freely. <br><br>&quot;We are getting nowhere, we need to leave one of these buggers alive to ask a damn question&quot; shouts Stingerfx<br><br>Unfortunately his pleas fall upon deaf ears as the roars of battle fill the air, he decides to take it into his own hands, he slowly begins to fall back, and slips into a small corridor to look for himself<br><br>He has very little luck trying to find anyone conscious enough to answer any questions, he just about gives up his solo search when a sole Tier'Dal walks out of a room nearby, he grabs an arrow and lines up his shot. The arrow pierces in the calf of the Dark Elf and the camouflage drops. Stingerfx charges and throws his fist into the chest of his opponent, winding him temporarily.<br><br>&quot;Yell for help and you die&quot; he muttered under his breath &quot;Now where is my wife&quot;<br><br>&quot;Urgh . . . she is being kept in the cells, the ones of the grand hall as far as I know&quot; was the reply &quot;please don't kill me&quot;<br><br>Stingerfx swung his fist, catching the dark elf around the head, rendering him unconscious.<br><br>&quot;Now to get Drexsys back&quot; he said, raising his camouflage<br><br><br>********************<br><br>Suddenly the main doors to the hall swing open and there he stands, the incarnation of evil, hatred in it's purest form, the Master<br><br>The Elves cower away in fright as he stares at them, he slowly brings his icy glare across Drexsys, and then onto Coranax &quot;So,&quot; he talks quietly, &quot;My control over you Coranax has been broken&quot;<br><br>Coranax snarls at him, and looks at Drexsys who is staring at him in total disbelief, &quot;You've been using your powers over these weak minded fools, an good idea, but you should know better than to try to fool me&quot;<br><br>&quot;Bah, you are just ass weak ass these ssoftskinss&quot; replied Coranax<br><br>The master begins to walk closer to Coranax, &quot;You could have had it all, power, riches, anything you wanted, I gave it to you on a platter&quot;<br><br>&quot;You used me ass an assassin, you wanted a back up plan to your first kidnapping, and you are sso unimaginative ass to try the ssame sstunt again&quot;<br><br>The master has started to circle the pair &quot;I saw your potential, I realized what you could do, but you failed me, I spend much time and resources on turning you into the perfect person to remove that damn bard and you failed me&quot;<br><br>Coranax whispers to Drexsys &quot;(Time)&quot; he turned and swung his spear, cutting the magic bracelet from her wrist, she feels the rush of magic return now that the restrain is removed, she quickly concentrates and begins to mutter.<br><br>&quot;She is casting Yonder stop her&quot;<br><br>Two Guards begin to run at her but it is too late, she fades away before they reach her<br><br>&quot;That is your last mistake Coranax&quot;<br><br>Coranax beams an evil grin then he charged at the master knocking him flat, rolling off as he did it, he made a run, but as he passes the guards one is able to make a side slash, cutting deep into his flank as he bursts out of the door<br><br>&quot;GET HIM NOW&quot; roars the master<br><br><br>********************<br><br>Drexsys still a little dizzy is struggling to cope with what she had been told, [memorize a shadow step? what does that mean?] that lizard, [what is he up to?]. She is shaken from her thoughts as she is dragged to a giant hall, Coranax is standing right next to her, &quot;Why have i been brought here?&quot;<br><br>The door swings open and a man stands there, evil seems to be emitted from deep within. He looks right at her, she returns the look and into his eyes she can see pain, suffering and hatred, she cringes away<br><br>He begins to talk, she is still dizzy, but one thing comes through 'my control has been broken' [Coranax has not been under his powers, he has done everything under his own will] she stares at him in disbelief.<br><br>She cant focus on anything else said, she is frozen over what she first heard, she thinks it over in her mind until he talks to her, &quot;(Time)&quot; that was the signal, she tried but the bracelet still prevented her from casting, then as if he could hear her thoughts broke the restrain. <br><br>She managed to regain her concentration and cast, instantly teleporting her from the room. She is in a small room, there is virtually no light, suddenly the door bursts open and standing there is not a figure of evil, but her beloved . . . Stingerfx.<br><br>They stare at each other for a moment before they embrace &quot;I knew you would come&quot; she was almost crying<br><br>&quot;As much as I would love to hold you forever, we need to leave&quot; he replied &quot;How did you escape?&quot; <br><br>&quot;Coranax helped me, I will explain once we are safely away&quot;<br><br>They left together and began the long run out, they were almost out as they approached the exit when a wall formed in front of them, they were blocked by a horde of Evil minions<br><br>Stingerfx draws his sword and prepares to fight his way out, as he draws the sword the wall of evil seems to lose its confidence and fear appears in their eyes. Getting pretty smug Stingerfx holds his sword and beckons any challenger. They begin to back down and then Stingerfx realizes, he turns to see the force of good standing behind him<br><br>&quot;(damn, well should have known)&quot; He turns back to the wall &quot;Lets leave&quot;<br><br>The wall backs down and leaves quickly, letting the Dragons and Candirians leave in peace, they make sufficient distance between themselves and the outpost, until they finally reach the Dragon's fort<br><br>When they return she is beckoned to tell the tale of her capture, but unfortunately she had fallen asleep during the journey<br><br>&quot;Let her rest, she will tell us when she is ready&quot;<br><br>The noise of cheering, glasses being struck together, screaming Gnomes and cursing Barbarian's can be heard well into the night.<br><br>As quickly as she had returned home, her memory of the events faded into shadowed darkness... A dark fog crept into her mind and little by little the events vanished, leaving her with no memory of the Knight's aid, Coranax's help in freeing her, or her meeting with the Master... As time passed, as it always does, she could see only dreams and broken nightmares, her limp form slumped over Coranax's shoulder, groggily climbing up on to Firegod for the first time, and vague visions of galloping through predawn Karanas. With parts of visions and dreams haunting her, she grew to hate Coranax.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>~~My treasures do not clink together or glitter; they gleam in the sun and neigh in the night~~</td></tr>
